  <section id="ask">
    <h2>What you can ask for</h2>
    <p class="sog-col">As a member, you have rights to see how the Nation is organized and how its money is handled. A few of the most useful, and where they come from:</p>
    <div class="sog-ask">
      <div class="sog-askcard">
        <h3>The current organizational chart</h3>
        <p>You can request the Nation's current org chart from the Chief Administrative Officer, who is required to keep it current and recommend it to Council.</p>
        <span class="cite">Financial Administration Law, s.20(3)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sog-askcard">
        <h3>The Schedule of Remuneration and the audited statements</h3>
        <p>What the Chief and Council are paid, and the Nation's audited consolidated financial statements, are public documents the Nation publishes each year.</p>
        <span class="cite">First Nations Financial Transparency Act (FNFTA)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sog-askcard">
        <h3>Conflict-of-interest disclosures</h3>
        <p>Councillors must file an annual conflict-of-interest disclosure with the CAO. You can ask whether these have been filed and how they are handled.</p>
        <span class="cite">Financial Administration Law, s.22</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sog-askcard">
        <h3>Records from Council</h3>
        <p>To ask Council directly for records, minutes, or a Band Council Resolution, write to the Council Secretariat, the office that manages Council's correspondence and records.</p>
        <span class="cite">via the Council Secretariat</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sog-why" style="margin-top: var(--gap-6)">
      <h3>Add your voice</h3>
      <p>Members have submitted a records request to Chief and Council asking, on the record, what the membership gains from the Nation's businesses and ventures, and who they serve. You can <a href="/support/records-request" style="color: var(--accent-deep); font-weight: 700;">add your name in support of that request &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="terms">
    <h2>Key terms</h2>
    <dl class="sog-gloss">
      <dt>Chief and Council</dt><dd>The elected government: the Chief plus twelve Councillors.</dd>
      <dt>Chief Administrative Officer (CAO) / Director of Operations</dt><dd>The most senior staff officer, over the department directors. Titled "Director of Operations" in the Nation's HR policy.</dd>
      <dt>Finance and Audit Committee</dt><dd>A committee required by the Financial Administration Law, with independent members, that oversees budgets, the audit, and financial reporting.</dd>
      <dt>Financial Administration Law (FAL, 2020)</dt><dd>The Nation's 2020 law, under the First Nations Fiscal Management Act, setting the rules for budgets, officers, committees, borrowing, and reporting.</dd>
      <dt>Government Business Enterprise (GBE)</dt><dd>A company a government owns or controls but that operates as a self-sustaining business. Sagamok's companies are reported this way.</dd>
      <dt>Director / Officer</dt><dd>A board member or senior officer of a company or, under the FAL, of the Nation's administration.</dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

